'''GH One TV''' is a [[Ghana]]-based entertainment TV channel, whose content includes lifestyle, music, fashion, series, children's programs, comedy, and tourism. It is now owned by Excellence In Broadcasting (EIB) Networks, which has broadcaster Nathaniel Kwabena Anokye Adisi, a.k.a. Bola Ray, as its CEO.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/news/business/on-the-rise-bola-ray-s-eib-network-acquires-ghone-tv-station-id4249036.html|title=Bola Ray’s EIB Network acquires GHOne TV Station|website=www.pulse.com.gh|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref> The station was formerly owned by Charter House Productions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/communication/television.php|title=Ghana Television Stations and Networks|website=www.ghanaweb.com|access-date=2016-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/media-center/media-houses|title=Media Houses - Government of Ghana|last=Government|first=Ghana|website=www.ghana.gov.gh|access-date=2016-09-06}}</ref>
According to a survey conducted by GeoPoll, GH One is the 5th most watched TV station in Ghana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanajuice.com/3934|title=10 Most Watched TV Stations In Ghana, Check Out The List|date=2015-12-01|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-06}}</ref>
